TAP N TWINE raced between horses early, fell back into the turn, angled out, bid five wide and came up empty. COOKIN ROSES vied outside to the turn and stopped.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Work All Week H. HAWTHORNE RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 107. Stakes Purse 75000. FOR THREE-YEAR-OLDS AND UPWARD. No nomination fee. Nominees to pay $300 to pass the entry box and an additional $450 to start, with $75,000 guaranteed to be divided 60 percent to the winning owner, 20 percent to second, 10 percent to third, 5 percent to fourth, 3 percent to fifth and 2 percent divided equally among the remaining finishers. Weights: Wednesday, July 19, 2023. Starters to be named through the entry box by the usual time of closing. Trophy to the winning owner. Nominations closed Thur sday, July 13, 2023 with 18.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: W W CANDY was a bit crowded at the start, raced outside, rallied on the turn, split horses in tight quarters and bumped leaving the turn, closed willingly and got up in the final strides. TAPE TO TAPE was hustled along to set the pace, drew off leaving the turn for a clear lead and was caught near the wire. WENT WEST was crowded at the start, pressed the pace inside, bid along the rail on the turn, shifted out, went willingly to the wire, didn't have enough late and settled for show in a good effort. MIDNIGHT ESCAPE pressed the pace three wide, fell back a bit on the turn, was in tight and bumped entering the stretch and continued to close. DEVIL'S TOWER bobbled at the start, advanced to the turn, was in tight and bumped entering the stretch, angled in and leveled off. NAVY SEAL veered out at the start, trailed the field and offered a mild bid only. KAVOD broke out, pressed the pace between horses, challenged for the lead on the turn, weakened and faded.
